  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Import your `custom.py` into your project.\r\n\r\n2. In `custom.py`, write the `keep_painting()` function. This function should:\r\n\r\n   * Have parameters for `this_painter` and `color`\r\n\r\n   * Use a `while` loop to continue painting while the `Painter` `can_move()`\r\n   \r\n   * At each step, paint the current space and move forward\r\n   \r\n   * After the loop ends, paint the final space\r\n\r\n3. Write the `move_to_next_row()` function.\r\n\r\n   * Have a parameter for `this_painter`\r\n\r\n   * If the `Painter` `is_facing_east()`, turn left, move forward one space, and turn left again.\r\n   \r\n   * If the `Painter` `is_facing_south()`, call your `turn_right(this_painter)` function, move forward one space, and turn right again.\r\n\r\n4. Save `custom.py` to your Backpack.\r\n\r\n5. In `main.py`, import your functions.\r\n\r\n6. Use your functions to navigate and paint the areas.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/1ea5fd39088265c5ef223c2fd9d278b3-u1l9-l4d.gif)",
